original: Linden, Oskar Georg, läroverksadjunkt, Jönköping, f. 6/7/92 i Jönköp. av Gustaf L. o. h. h. f. Håkansson. G. 21 m. Karin Lund. Barn: Gerd f. 23, Ragnar 25. — Studiex. i Jönköp. n, fil. mag. i Upps. 16, pr o vår i Sthlm 19. Vik. adj. v. Jönköp. h. a. 1. 16-17, e. lär. v. Jakobs realsk. i Sthlm 17-18, vik. adj. i Strängnäs 18, e. lär. v. norra latin i Sthilm 19-22, e. lär. v. Jönköp. h. a. 1. 22-29, adj. i moders-ni., tyska o. eng. där sed. 29.
translated: Linden, Oskar Georg, high school teacher, Jönköping, born on July 6, 1892 in Jönköping, son of Gustaf L. and his wife Håkansson. Married on May 21 to Karin Lund. Children: Gerd born in 1923, Ragnar born in 1925. Completed exams in Jönköping, graduated with a Bachelor's degree in Uppsala in 1916, worked as a substitute teacher in Stockholm in 1919. Temporary teacher in Jönköping from 1916-1917, primary school teacher at Jakobs realskola in Stockholm from 1917-1918, substitute teacher in Strängnäs in 1918, primary school teacher at norra latin in Stockholm from 1919-1922, primary school teacher in Jönköping from 1922-1929, and has been a teacher in the subjects of mother tongue, German, and English there since 1929.
